summary: Report: Brie Larson Calls Off Her Engagement to Alex Greenwald Following Nearly Three Years
title: Report: Brie Larson Calls Off Her Engagement to Alex Greenwald Following Nearly Three Years
body:
Getty

Brie Larson has reportedly called off her engagement to Alex Greenwald following nearly three years, according to PEOPLE.

A source told PEOPLE, “they have taken a step back from their engagement for the time being but they remain close.”

Via PEOPLE:

The actress got engaged to Greenwald, 39, in May 2016 following several years of dating.

Greenwald joined her at numerous awards seasons events that year when Larson received recognition for the 2015 thriller Room. She even gave Greenwald a shout-out while accepting the Academy Award for best actress at the 2016 Oscars.

“Jacob Tremblay, my partner through this in every way possible,” she said of her Room costar. “My real partner, Alex Greenwald, I love you.”

Before getting a special shout-out during speech, Larson told Entertainment Tonight at the Screen Actors Guild Awards, “He’s the other half of the equation – how can you explain support? I mean, it goes beyond anything. He’s just my person, he’s my best friend.”

Here’s more from PEOPLE:

The two kept their relationship relatively private over the following years, but they did share that he serenaded the Captain Marvel star on her 29th birthday last year.

“That was the most beautiful rendition of ‘Happy Birthday’ I’ve ever heard,” Larson said with a laugh in a video on her Instagram story in October.

As for now, neither Brie or Greenwald has confirmed their split.

summary: Seriously, I can't understand why people are judging Captain Marvel when this damn movie isn't out yet! Why the hell someone...
body:
Seriously, I can’t understand why people are judging Captain Marvel when this damn movie isn’t out yet! Why the hell someone should hate or love something without knowing it?

Yes, you can be thrilled but calling it the best Marvel movie… WHY? HOW? on what grounds?

And NO, she’s not gonna replace Captain America. They are really different and that’s something you can notice from the trailer.

And OBVIOUSLY she doesn’t smile in the poster… I mean, she’s in the middle of some sort of intergalactic war, what’s funny?? Also, this is a superhero movie, people… can you name just ONE Marvel poster in which the hero is smiling? I can think just of Loki smiling in a Thor poster and obviously he’s not the hero and that’s some sort of evil smile, soo… Why should she smile? ̶I̶ ̶d̶i̶d̶n̶'̶t̶ ̶w̶a̶n̶t̶ ̶t̶o̶ ̶b̶r̶i̶n̶g̶ ̶u̶p̶ ̶t̶h̶i̶s̶ ̶b̶u̶t̶ ̶I̶ ̶c̶a̶n̶'̶t̶ ̶h̶e̶l̶p̶ ̶m̶y̶s̶e̶l̶f̶ ̶b̶e̶c̶a̶u̶s̶e̶ ̶t̶h̶i̶s̶ ̶i̶s̶ ̶t̶h̶e̶ ̶f̶u̶c̶k̶i̶n̶ ̶t̶r̶u̶t̶h̶ Because she’s a woman? “YoU aRe prEtTier when u SmilE” SHUT UP! SHE DOESN’T NEED TO SMILE TO BE BEAUTIFUL AND SHE DOESN’T EVEN NEED TO BE BEAUTIFUL, SHE JUST NEED TO BE POWERFUL AND TO KICK SKRULLS ASSES

Also, have people already forget Brie Larson’s brilliant replay with those creepy smiling superhero posters? Lol
